<div>
  <p>
    We provide a single package containing the server and the client tools. For a
    standard server setup, download the package <strong>Server</strong> and
    install it using the package manager. You do not need the client tools.

    The <strong>Client Tools</strong> package only contains the tools, like arangosh,
    arangodump, but nor the server. Use this in case you are already running
    ArangoDB on a different machine and want to connect to that server from a
    client machine.

    As an alternative there is a <strong>Tar</strong> containing the server and
    client tools which can be install in any location and which does not
    require root rights for installation.
  </p>
  <hr/>
  <p class="ara_package_line">Packages for the <strong>Debian</strong> package manager:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="@DOWNLOAD_LINK@/arangodb34/@DOWNLOAD_EDITION@/Linux/@DEBIAN_NAME_SERVER@">Server @ARANGODB_VERSION@</a><br>
      (@DEBIAN_SIZE_SERVER@ MByte, SHA256 @DEBIAN_SHA256_SERVER@)
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="@DOWNLOAD_LINK@/arangodb34/@DOWNLOAD_EDITION@/Linux/@DEBIAN_NAME_CLIENT@">Client Tools @ARANGODB_VERSION@</a><br>
      (@DEBIAN_SIZE_CLIENT@ MByte, SHA256 @DEBIAN_SHA256_CLIENT@)
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="@DOWNLOAD_LINK@/arangodb34/@DOWNLOAD_EDITION@/Linux/@DEBIAN_NAME_DEBUG_SYMBOLS@">Debug Symbols @ARANGODB_VERSION@</a><br>
      (@DEBIAN_SIZE_DEBUG_SYMBOLS@ MByte, SHA256 @DEBIAN_SHA256_DEBUG_SYMBOLS@)
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="ara_package_line"><strong>Tar</strong> based packages:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="@DOWNLOAD_LINK@/arangodb34/@DOWNLOAD_EDITION@/Linux/@TARGZ_NAME_SERVER@">Server @ARANGODB_VERSION@</a><br>
      (@TARGZ_SIZE_SERVER@ MByte, SHA256 @TARGZ_SHA256_SERVER@)
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>
